name: Cocoa Land Bali
address: Jl Raya Denpasar Bedugul, Mekarsari, Kec. Baturiti, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82191, Indonesia
review 1: Cocoa Land Bali is a chocolate lover's paradise! With an impressive array of organic chocolate varieties, they've got something to suit every taste bud. What sets them apart is their unique packages, offering not just delicious treats but also cocoa farming education and chocolate molding sessions topped with a scrumptious lunch. The store itself is a delight to explore, with impeccable presentation and testers available for all their flavors. Bonus points for the fantastic playground and ample parking ‚Äì making it a win-win for both kids and adults alike!
review 2:
Thank you ! It was an amazing experience, we enjoyed the tour, educational material and the tasting.

We paid 115 IDR per person for the tour and making chocolate. They were ok with only one paying, the one that will make the chocolate.

Thank you, highly recommend this place
review 3: Great for studying cocoa.Highly maintained and also have a souvenir shop.The education program has facilities cocoa tree and machine replicas.
review 4: The have backyard for kids play and good place to learn how to make chocolate.
review 5:
We had a fun despite there is practically nothing to see. There is exposition of some machines. We have got short explanation close to cocoa tree with cocoa been and they let you taste it, then you can play with melted chocolate and get 6 pralines out of it actually maybe done before as not enough time to cool down. Half of surface is a big souvernirs shop.

Maybe with kids it could be more engaging but for adults you can skip.

Aftertaste is that chocolate you taste and buy are different. It is also not true chocolate but rather chocolate like product in EU sense. Also you can buy it somewhere else on Bali.

If I would knew it before I would skip visiting this shop.

name: Babi Guling Depot Betty '2'
address: J5FV+PFQ, Jl. Mekarsari - Baturiti Bedugul, Mekarsari, Kec. Baturiti, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82191, Indonesia
review 1: Men Bety 2 is a hidden delight ‚Äì the flavors are next level delicious! Sure, the space is a bit snug, but let's talk about that super-friendly service ‚Äì OMG, I'm in love! The warmth they bring to the table is almost as delightful as their dishes. If you're into tasty bites and a side of incredible service, Men Bety 2 is the spot. üíïüçú
review 2: Crowded during holiday, easy access cos it is in a main road. Please make sure you're not in a hurry. Good taste, good food. There are some others around, funny pig statues on the wall.
review 3: Insane! This is the best ever. It is perfect in every part. The soup, the rice, the pork. All of them are perfectly delicious. For 5 packages (nasi campur + soup) + 5 hot tea only 125.000 rupiah. That was crazy cheap
review 4: This is undoubtly THE BEST babi guling in the entire Bali. I tried all the others, and they tasted fine. But this one is HEAVENLY. I will undoubtedly drive all those miles fron kuta just to eat one portion of this babi guling. And I encourage everyone to do the same.
review 5: Enak sekali, absolutely delicious. Locals only joint, beats the tourist stop. The all mixed platter with rice is about Rupiah 25k, which is a good bargain as you get to taste different cuts of the meat. Also loved the accompanying soup!!

review 2: Its a camping ground. Very cold at night before sunrise. Great place for outdoors or overnight camping.
review 3: Too noisy, noisy karaoke, it's almost midnight and they keep going, can't sleep
review 4: If you're coming to Bali, or even Balinese themselves, try this place at least once. They have great views, from mountain to rice field you can see it here. Say you're Nature lovers but you never came here? Nah

name: Ayam Betutu Gilimanuk
address: J5CV+JR3, Jalan Bedugul, Mekarsari, Kec. Baturiti, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 80191, Indonesia
review 1: Best Ayam Betutu on the way to Bedugul! Must try if you travel to Bali North.
review 2: Spicy chicken and duck from gili manuk west bali is my favorite food while visiting bali. DONT EVER TRY it if you cant eat spicy food. I tried the sate lilit that given for free by the chef. The taste is yummy. This is an option if you dont like spicy food. The warung is my first option for betutu when we are not in gili manuk. I like men tempeh betutu the most.
review 3: Had quick dinner here. The presentation could have been better and it should be served in standard recipe. We ordered Ayam Betutu 1/4 but it came up with very dry fried chicken with small size. And it was quite pricey. Not exactly what we expected from the regular Ayam Betutu. However their service and hospitality were unquestionable. Hope they improved the taste.
review 4:
Good warung food. I was attracted there by the look of the place and big flags at the entry. I wasn't impressed by the food.
I couldn't pay by card. Their machine wasn't working.
review 5: Good food, but when I went there, most of the menus weren't available unfortunately.

name: Hidden Paradise Bali Peneng
address: Mekarsari, Baturiti, Tabanan Regency, Bali 82191, Indonesia
review 1:
We stayed here for 2 days and I was really impressed by this place! Peaceful and cozy, with great food and amazing service!
Also, there are several waterfalls just in 10 min ride. You won‚Äôt get bored for sure üòçüëç
review 2: Thomas and his family are very kind people, they don‚Äôt bother you at all while still looking after you at the same time. The food is very delicious even though they do not include any meat other than tuna, all the food tastes like authentic Italian food. The location is amazing if you have a rented car or motorcycle due to the many places to visit nearby. Thomas makes most of his ingredients himself and sources them from his own garden. Overall our stay was very good and I would recommend to anyone who does not want to always stay in the city in Bali
review 3: Our family spent 3 nights here. Absolutely love it. We enjoyed the food, the view and good talk with Thomas, the owner. We walked to the water stream, only 10 minutes walk.  The location is perfect, only 5 minutes drive from the main road, but very quite and surrounded by bamboo forest, and vast farm. Defenitely will be coming back.
review 4: It‚Äòs an actual paradise! It‚Äôs so quite and nice. Directly in nature and the hosts are very welcoming. We enjoyed our 4 nights of relaxation and enjoyed the organic and self made Italien food.
review 5:
Thomas
Dear owner , father of Lalita and Kiki
Hidden Paradise -organic vanilla farm.
I want to thank and thank your family Thomas for your hospitality! Your territory is very sincere, fabulously sweet, beautiful, well-groomed, clean! Each item has its place and purpose, your items on the territory are all with soul, they are animated by your attention to them and care with love! your place has a soul and a heart, vanilla farm is a very magnetic, energetically capacious place, restorative, giving you the opportunity to reboot, be alone with yourself and at the same time feel the care of you and your children! your pets help you relax and feel natural love! The morning mantras pleasantly awakened me and gave me the joy of being, the morning coffee made by you, the owner of the space, awakened in me a whole world of perception of myself and everything around me, warmth appeared in my heart, I began to come to life and see with my heart the beauty in everything that exists! Your family warmed my soul and I felt calmer. Because of the war in my country, I am worried, and now, after a long time, I feel calmer from visiting you! This is very valuable to me. May harmony, love, happiness always reside in your soul, heart, in your family, in your villa in your garden, wherever you are Thomas!

P.s.
I wrote through a translator, so excuse me if the translation is not very competent, I think that with my heart I conveyed everything I wanted to your heart, thank you for being there. With respect and love, Rosa Derman is from Ukraine

name: Pondok Peneng
